    Module:

        global.xml

    Abstract:

        This the global navigation file for the site. It maps out the
        navigation bar links for each page.

    Tags:

        navbar - This element corresponds to a page that begins a new category
                 for the web site. Examples include Products, Contact, Links.

        global - This is an element that will appear in every page on the site.
                 Usually reserved for top level pages.

    Attributes:

        name - Display name for the navbar category. It appears on the 
               navigation bar in the page. Example: Contacts
        
        link - Hyperlink setting for the navbar category.

        file - File name of the build file that will be this page.


-->



